In these remarks, President Trump discusses allegations that his campaign was spied on. He claims that there is proof of this and suggests that serious misconduct occurred. He criticizes former FBI Director James Comey and expresses hope that the allegations are not true, but believes it will become apparent after reviewing the evidence. Trump also mentions a meeting with the Department of Justice and Congress to address the issue. He asserts that he is not undercutting the Justice Department, but rather cleaning up a terrible situation. The President also briefly mentions the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) negotiations and a potential summit with North Korea. He emphasizes the need for transparency in these matters.